Since the Western countries imposed sanctions on Russia, the U.S. government has repeatedly pressured some neutral nations to choose side. It seems that if one doesn't go against Russia, one does not stand on the right side of history. However, throughout its history, the U.S. has repeatedly waged wars against sovereign nations under the pretext of "justice," but is actually based on hegemonism and mighty politics. Editors: Sudeshna Sarkar, Yuan Xin Senior producer: Wei Wei Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)